textDisplay:
The "we need more fathers"-thing doesn't help. You won't get more black fathers, at least not in the next 10 000 years. Sounds wacky, but I am not pulling that out of my ass. This is going to be a long comment, but I think those who read it, won't regret it, even if they disagree, because then they can tell me how and why I am wrong and that is fun too, isn't it?

So as far as we can tell, humans developed in Africa and spread to the rest of the world from there.
Sub-Saharan Africa, despite having some smaller deserts, is overall a very fertile and lush place with a very stable climate.
Parts of it are outright paradisaical, not in a Caribbean palm beach sense, but in a "you can feed yourself by just plucking fruit from a tree"-sense.
Naturally and logically, the earliest humans settled those places first.

As I said, in those places, it is easy to feed yourself and your kids with little effort. That means women didn't really need help from a male provider to do it.
Accordingly they developed Matriarchal societies.
A real Matriarchy is not what most people have in mind when they hear the word, no "Femdom" fantasy and no Amazonian Warrior Women from Venus in silver leotards or grass skirts and coconut bras, enslaving Earth Astronauts and learning what "love" is from them.

A Matriarchy is just a society where the women don't need male providers and form the core of the group, raising the children and doing most of the work, while the men exist at the rim of society, doing their own thing, sitting under a tree, making music, drinking "ant beer" out of a calabash and occasionally chasing away a predator.
They are like a herd of elephants, basically.

And like a herd of elephants, they practice "Tournament Sexuality", instead of "Peer Bonding".
Women don't need male providers, so they have no reason to put up with a Beta.
Like in the herd of elephants, only the biggest, strongest, most attractive dudes get invited into the huts to make more babies.

The work force of the Beta men lays dormant, which is why Matriarchies never amount to much, civilization-wise.
In many parts of Africa and to a lesser extend in parts of Asia and South-America, you can still find such Matriarchal societies exist today.

The fossil record and DNA science support the hypothesis that for a while, in those African paradises, all humans lived like that. The number of Double-Y chromosome Alpha men was way higher early on. Only about 10 to 13 000 years ago, that number dropped.

At some point mankind ran out of paradises to settle and people needed to move out into the less hospitable areas.
There a woman couldn't feed herself and her kids without the help of a man anymore.
That is when the Patriarchy was invented.

Women hired those formally useless Beta men to do the extra work necessary to feed them and their kids and they paid for it with sex and offspring.
This caused an explosion in human productivity and the first well organized city building higher civilizations started popping up.

Unlike what Feminists say, Patriarchy is not some shadowy evil force, randomly created by men to keep women down, it is nothing else but the result of the adaptation of Peer Bonding Sexuality and ultimately it is created by women, when they chose to team up with the Beta men to not raise their kids alone anymore.
Every higher civilization in human history was and is built on that unwritten "Labor for Sex/Offspring" contract.

That is why we shame promiscuous women and lazy men. It isn't a double standard. Promiscuous men and lazy women are no problem, because they don't break the contract at the heart of civilization. They aren't a corrosive force. Women who give away the goods for free lower the market value of pussy and men who refuse to work and pay for it, are useless. It is a female perspective and why we have a problem with it. As paradoxical as it might seem, Patriarchy is ultimately a gynocentric construct. Invented by females for the benefit of females.

This may seem like a crazy long, rambling tangent or maybe even totally off topic, but it is not. I had to lay the conceptual foundation for what is coming next.

People who talk about it have the tendency to lose their careers and be silenced, but deep down most Americans across the political spectrum think the reason why black Americans tend to be tall and athletic is because they were bred that way during the age of slavery.

That isn't true. First of all, that age of slavery was too short. You can't get those kinds of lasting results within the few generations it lasted. More importantly though, you would have needed a well organized and coordinated breeding program, where you separate males from females to prevent "wild breeding" and only allow the specimen you deep promising to have offspring, in order to do it.
No, there was no such breeding program in the New World.

There was one in Africa though, within those Matriarchal tribes and it was running for many thousands of years.

The inherent dynamics and conditions of a Tournament Sexuality exclude the vast majority of males from the breeding process. When women have no need for a provider, what other criteria than size, strength, muscles, general attractiveness, combat performance and genital size could they use to determine which man's children to bear?
Of course they bred aggressive Double-Y chromosome Alpha men in those Matriarchies.
That is why it is called "Tournament Sexuality".

So why aren't all Africans tall and athletic? Why are most Africans rather scrawny and average by greater human standards, while African Americans tend to be bigger and more athletic?

The reason is that most modern Africans are the descendants of those later Patriarchal tribes which developed in the less hospital lands. As I explained, because they used all that formally dormant Beta male productivity, they grew bigger, better organized and more civilized than the Matriarchal tribes.

Most African Americans are the descendants of the Matriarchal tribes though, because those big, strong Alpha men they produced fetched the best prizes on the slave markets and they didn't have big, well organized armies to defend themselves, when their Patriarchal neighbors came to farm them and sell them to the Arab and white slavers.

The consequence is that this is a ethnicity that never went through the 10 000 year long process of "Patriarchalization" or however you want to call it. They never domesticated themselves like other groups, they never adopted Peer Bonding, they never learned to live in large groups and control their impulses.

The concept of the Nuclear Family is not in their genes.

Look at "The Hood".
They still operate exactly like those Matriarchal African Villages.
The women run the homes and raise the kids alone, while the men hang out somewhere in groups, separated from them.
Instead of a abundantly fertile nature providing easy food to the females in the African jungle, it is the welfare system that allows them to get by without a male provider.
And the men, instead of sitting under a tree, making music and playing some board game, hang around on the parking lots of convenient stores.

Not all black people, obviously, but not all of them are from the Matriarchies. Of course some people from the Patriarchal tribes got sold as slaves too and their descendants have less problems integrating into a Patriarchal society, because their ancestors went through the 10 000 year long self-domestication process, like the Europeans who built the USA.

I'm not shitting on black Americans.
We all are reverting back to Matriarchy, because the success of Patriarchy basically, for all intents and purposes, turned the whole world into one of those fertile African paradises, through welfare and by raising the gerneral living standards for everyone.
In this regard, fundamentally it isn't much of a difference whether a young black man hangs around on the street all day, or whether a young white man sits in his room, playing video games all day. Both are conceptually returning back to the shade of that African tree at the outskirt of the village, to sit there, while the women run society without them and while a hand full of Alpha men do all the fucking.

Matriarchy is our natural default state and we are sliding back into it, now that Patriarchy served its purpose, I'm afraid.
For whites and Asians and some other groups, the slide is just longer, because they have been living in Patriarchies for much longer.

So those calls for "more fathers" are totally useless and ignorant.
Being fathers and having fathers is a relatively new invention, on a greater evolutionary scale and even those ethnic groups who trained themselves that behavior over 10 000 years, are slowly losing it again, because women don't need those fathers anymore and they don't care whether their kids are better off with them or not.

To the Protesters Who Got Violent,

Every one of those businesses you shuttered, that was a job for a low income person. Many of which were immigrants. That was the difference between food and homelessness. Downtown Portland, though it looks flashy, is mostly populated by very poor people, many of which are disabled or people of color, and most of those places you looted offer retail jobs. Often, even bank tellers start with minimum wage. That night, when you thought you were changing the world, many of you instead, crushed families' hopes of returning to work, and feeding their children.

textDisplay:
I grew up in New Jersey and well remember the riots in Newark and Plainfield that took place in the late 1960's. Those used to be great places to live, especially Plainfield, which had big beautiful homes, nice stores, and good schools.
They were both ruined in the space of a few weeks of rioting AND HAVE NEVER RECOVERED.
I have been coming down to Portland from the Seattle area for the last 15 years to shop because you have no sales tax. We have 10+%. I also love the hotels and restaurants.
Portland has declined radically in that time period and, if my experience with the burnt out cities of the Northeast is any guide, will take decades to come back...if it ever does.
I can't think of a single American city that has gone this route and come back.
This is not only a failure of leadership, it is deliberate. Portland, Seattle, San Francisco, Los Angeles, etc. ALL run by people who believe in nothing except catering to the needs of the most antisocial citizens, largely because they're antisocial themselves.

Sometimes, maintaining the peace requires more people with boots on the ground to handle such a large crowd with a few instigators hiding like cowards within a peaceful group. Having a large enough enforcement team, visible on the streets to let the instigators know, "we're watching you".
On the flip side, I don't 100% trust police or the military to maintain and unbiased stance and perform their jobs without taking it personally. We need calm and experienced leaders in charge of this enforcement team(s). I've been seeing more and more videos showing the police and national guard overreaching their authority. That type of behavior is going to encourage more violence, and probably include personal firearms entering the equation. A "large" police and national guard presence will significantly deter the would be instigators from even thinking about causing violence.

I'm sure there is some sort of equation that gives an idea of the ratio of how many police officers you need, for how many protesters to maintain control. You know as well as I do that Trump WILL bring in the military, so you're probably not going to avoid it. textDisplay:
You blame the Governor for that? I was a product of our schools in the 1990s and honestly my quality of education suffered because of other children at my school.
Not the government in so far as the government is defined as Salem, what was going on at the capitol or in the governors mansion, what was wrong was a much more local problem.
I was Autistic, no one knew, I was hospitalized at about the age of 7 in Providence medical center where essentially my parents consented to the school being able to talk to my doctors because from their vantage point they were desperate to prove I was disabled.
I did not eat hospital food, my psychatrist not being educated into sensory processing disorders merely assumed that my not eatting anything but breakfast was an attempt to test how far I could push things in disobedience, I was forced to stare at plates of food for 2 hours for the entire extended periods they set out for lunch merely because everything on the plate disgusted me, my mom at one point snuck food into my concerned and my stupid dumbshit of a father tattle taled on her for some inconceivably stupid reason. At some point I was taken in for an MRI for testing and too jittery for the machine to capture it's images because I moved around too much so they kept me up for 24 hours watching television and movies and then tried again and STILL failed.
Eventually out of concern for my not eatting my mother pulled me out AMA and in the discussions with doctors there was a confrontation because they said nothing was wrong with me and that the MRI results showed no abnormalities and that my problems were more my mothers codependence- this would have been fine if things ended there but what followed was about 5 or 6 years of torment in my childhood to my adolescence that only ended after I left the city and began to travel around the country. I will never forget. I was bullied intensely by my peers, I only got diagonsed with Asperger's at the age of13 and every time I tried to tell my teachers who are who I blame for the dropout rates they basically gave me lectures about dealing with difficult people and would not punish my bullies, or if they did was a slap on the wrist ,very rarely particularly harsh unless they witnessed it happen and even sitll rather than do anything that would FORCE their childs parents to to stop with their "boys will be boys defenses of their bullshit like an out of school suspension for the kids targetting me and a stern telling to their parents that that excuse will NOT be accepted and to teach their kids not to bully other children- it never happened. it never came. They Fucked up, my grades suffered. I was depressed, I basically lusted for death and only escape onto the internet where my few "REal friends" existed did anything to cheer me up. Who failed me? misses larson, misses smith, Whoever whatsherfucking face the british old hag teaching 6th.... She failed me, As well as the red haired one as I was moved from classroom to classroom unlike other kids until I ended up in the only half way decent classroom with misses macintosh who I still remember and respect but the other 3 I honestly want to eliminate their pensions entirely. and if that means those three end up homeless and dead I will piss on their graves. same to misses larson and smith. they failed me miserably and I wish I just had not have gone at all.
"well meaning adults" failed to protect the innocent from other children tormenting me. My point is merely Governor Brown or the Then governor back in the 1990s had nothing to do with my problems. Jackson Elementaries teachers were the problem. My point is merely that Kate brown isn't necessarily at fault for our failing schools.

textDisplay: We all wear EMS tactical pants, they have pockets for our gear... A lot of us wear vests because people shoot at uniforms... Pulse check is nationally trained for 10 seconds or less... His condition is obvious... EMS does not freak out in front of people... We are supposed to stay calm... The murderer is the one that performed the incorrect lift, not the EMS... And you don't fool around on scene, you get them to the best emergency care you can, as fast as you can, and you try with everything you have, to undo what the murderer did while in route to the hospital. Pray for these people that are trying to help him... We need it...  We arrive in all kinds of situations... We never know exactly what we are coming in to...  We are just as shocked, and in just as much disbelief over 4 officers murdering George as the rest of the normal people in the world.  It should have never happened!  We in EMS are here to help people.  CPR at the scene, should have happened right after the 4 minute mark... It should have continued until EMS took over...  It should have never been needed in the first place!  Almost no one comes back without being brain dead... And considering how long he was down without oxygen, he most likely would have had serious mental and physical deficits... It should have started immediately... When the murderer wiggled and placed more pressure on George's neck to see if George would react, and he realized that George was dead, everything else was him trying to save face and pretend that he didn't just murder George... They knew that the situation would have rapidly gotten worse with the public that was right... Even though I think these people would have jumped right in and started CPR  on George before turning on the murderer... These men were scared little wimps that couldn't step up and do the right thing, when they knew they should...  The murderer must have also been a superior in rank that they didn't step up and stop him... They are all guilty... They have plenty of other ways they could have handled the entire situation from the beginning, and plenty of other choices of equipment to use on someone resisting. textDisplay: This is one of the most heart wrenching, soul crushing things I have ever seen.  Everything about this video is wrong.  This poor person should've never been treated this way, and regardless of what had allegedly happened before the recording during the initial encounter, there is no reason on God's green earth that the officer should've remained pressing his knee into this person's neck after they lost consciousness. You could see the involuntary muscle spasms of their body that you would see with brain death.  How many more times does this have to happen before we finally get it together.  Something needs to change, this is a symptom of a much deeper problem and I'm not sure that it's racism.  It very well could be, but I think the root could possibly be training or this specific group or clique of officer's police culture.  Or it could've been this one individual who was simply unfit to serve as a police officer due to some unknown unknown underlying issue, such as a lack of training or something more basic is just lack of regard for human life from maybe being burned out or numb to previous personal trauma that was left untreated and manifested itself into this bizarre and murderous behavior.  But that doesn't explain the other officers, you could tell the one interacting with the by standers was not in control of the situation and was scared, and did the equivalent of freezing up when they should've taken righteous action to halt their fellow officer from unjustifiabley killing this person.  You could see the panic on the officers face who was interacting with the by standers.  What's that saying?  Something about idle hands do the devil's work or some shit?  That's basically what happened here.  Not one of the officers there had the courage to check their peer; that cost George Floyd his life.  I hope his family and the community can recover in a healthy way from this tragic event.  I hope the police departments will learn from it, like really break it down, all of the components or lack thereof that had to be present for this to happen the way it did and thoroughly analyze the events that lead up to this happening and implement changes to keep this from happening again to someone elses partner, son, or brother, friend.  Then share their findings with the other police communities and an action plan on how to address the root cause of this terrible pattern we are seeing.  I think this would need to be done both independently and within the department internally, separately from each other, and then comparing the findings of the two independent investigations.  I hope that everyone involved and affected by this can heal in a positive way, and I completely understand the reason now for everything I have been reading about with the protests.   If you're still reading this, be well and stay up.

George Floyd was murdered for allegedly using a counterfeit bill, which turned out to be a legitimate bill. Now there are protests and riots that are turning violent. If there's no justice how can you expect peace.

The system needs significant reform. There needs to be new police protocols. This should have been a simple conversation between citizens to understand the situation. However what we saw was a coward murder an innocent man.

textDisplay:
It amazes me how many people here want these cops in prison NOW with no trial, no investigation, and no coroners report. You sure all of you want to live in a society where we get rid of trials and investigations? Like where if you buy a used car and maybe the previous owner had a ecstasy pill that fell between the seats and you get pulled over and they find it, we have no investigation, no trial, and you go straight to prison... That's where you want to live???

If the investigation shows this man died from blood circulation or oxygen being cut off to his brain, I absolutely agree the officers should be charged and receive prison time. But playing devil's advocate, what if we find out George Floyd was on drugs and maybe had a underlying medical condition and coincidentally had a heart attack or stroke during the stress of this situation? Do we send these men to prison because George Floyd took drugs and broke the law? Keep in mind if you say yes to this, it sets a precedence that you too could go to prison for some similar situation. Say you get into a simple shoving match with someone in a parking lot over a parking space, and the other guy has a underlying heart condition and has a heart attack and dies after you shove him... Are you going to be ok going to prison for this?

My point is I hope everyone stops having knee jerk reactions to all this and thinks things through logically and waits for the results of the investigation and coroner's report. Then based on those facts, make a rational choice on what to do and understand that whatever we choose to do to these officers as a society will be applied to us if we ever end up in the same situation.

textDisplay: I‚Äôve been on the fence with acouple of these incidents being able to understand both sides. Usually siding with the victims but sometimes with the officers. But this was undoubtedly murder. Even if he didn‚Äôt intend to kill that man. Improper restraint, indifference to the welfare of his detainee, no self awareness or awareness to his suspects pleas for help. The man was in handcuffs, face down on the street, with 2 officers holding him down and a 3rd on crowd control. They were in no danger. George apologized for resisting being put in the car and swore he would cooperate if the officer would let him breath. People around them begging for this mans life. When the man went limp that should have been a clue. When George peed himself that is a tell tale sign that his heart may have just stopped. They all should face serious consequences but the officer who killed george should be charged with murder. Or manslaughter at the very very least. The camera man said something I thought was prophetic, he said your going to realize that you just stood there and let a man die and your going to have nightmares about that and it‚Äôs going to haunt you for the rest of your life. textDisplay: This is so disturbing. I couldn't stop watching, but I wish I had. Never want to see someone die a slow death of suffocation ever again. You could see the moment he lost consciousness, the moment hypoxic spasms began, and you can even infer when his heart stopped beating. Those are universally recognizable signs that a person is dying. Not only was this use of force unwarranted, it's not a part of police training. Self defense and hand to hand combat instructors won't teach this, because this is something you do to kill people. If any of these racist monsters could've swallowed their perverted pride in that moment and listened to bystanders, this tragedy could have been avoided. My only hope is that this video brings about some real justice
